.next/
node_modules/
*.local
.env

# out/ (the built static export) is intentionally ignored: it is a
# generated build artifact, not source. It is NOT committed to the
# repository -- keeping the repo to source-code-and-docs is what keeps
# `git clone` lightweight. The prebuilt frontend instead ships inside
# offline release bundles (ConfigFoundry-Offline-vX.Y.Z.zip, built by
# scripts/build_release_bundle.sh), which is where an install that
# needs zero Node.js should come from. Building from a plain git clone
# needs Node once (`make build`) to produce this directory locally.
# See docs/airgap.md and docs/installation.md.
out/
